This paper focuses on analyzing the language content of earnings calls and its impact on financial analysts' decision making. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and predicting financial data, which falls under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also touches on the topic of cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it mentions private communication with company executives, which could involve sensitive information.
